# CyberPravda Frontend — Project Context

## Overview
CyberPravda is a debate/opinion platform where users create **topics**, propose **versions** (of arguments/positions), write **arguments**, and submit **opinions**. The frontend talks to an external REST API backend — there is no CMS (no Sanity) in this repo.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework:** Next.js 15 (App Router) with React 18, TypeScript 5
- **Package manager:** Yarn 4.9.2 (Corepack)
- **Auth:** Clerk (`@clerk/nextjs` v6) — middleware in `src/middleware.tsx`, provider in `src/core/providers/RootProviders/`
- **Data fetching:** TanStack React Query v5 (prefetch + dehydrate in Server Components, `useQuery`/`useMutation` on client)
- **HTTP client:** Axios (`src/core/api/client.ts`), base URL from `NEXT_HTTP_URL`
- **Client state:** Redux Toolkit (`src/store/`) for UI slices (user, arguments, toast)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4 (`@theme` in `globals.scss`) + SCSS Modules (`.module.scss`) + `classnames` + `tailwind-merge`
- **Motion:** Framer Motion
- **DnD:** @dnd-kit
- **Icons:** lucide-react
- **i18n:** i18next + react-i18next — locales `en`, `ru`, `es` — JSON files in `public/locales/`
- **SEO:** next-sitemap
- **Build output:** `standalone` mode, deployed via systemd on port 6062

## Architecture (FSD-inspired layers)

```
src/
├── app/              # Next.js App Router: routes, layouts, global styles, fonts
│   ├── [locale]/     # Locale-prefixed routes (topics, versions, arguments, new-opinion, search, sign)
│   ├── styles/       # SCSS theme partials (_colors, _typo, _radius, _shadows, _paddings)
│   └── globals.scss  # Tailwind v4 entry, @theme tokens, global utility classes
├── core/             # Shared infrastructure
│   ├── api/          # Axios client, API classes (TopicApi, ArgumentApi, VersionsApi, ProfileApi), hooks, models
│   ├── constants/    # App-wide constants
│   ├── models/       # Domain models (Topic, Argument, Version, Opinion, Author)
│   ├── providers/    # ReactQuery, Redux Store, Root providers
│   └── utils/        # Cookies, meta, paths, authors
├── i18n/             # i18next config, client/server init, locale manager
├── libs/             # Reusable utilities
│   ├── hooks/        # Shared hooks
│   ├── ui-components/# Primitive UI (Card, Button, Modal, Skeleton, Tabs, Toast, etc.)
│   └── utils/        # String/date helpers
├── store/            # Redux store + slices (userslice, argumentsSlice, toastSlice)
├── types/            # Global TS declarations (scss.d.ts)
├── widgets/          # Domain-specific composite UI
│   ├── AppHeader/
│   ├── Arguments*/ ArgumentsList/ ArgumentsTabs/
│   ├── TopicsList/
│   ├── Versions*/ VersionView/
│   ├── Opinion*/
│   ├── PageWidgets/  # Page-scoped widget bundles (HomePageWidgets, TopicPageWidgets, etc.)
│   └── ...
└── middleware.tsx     # Clerk middleware
```

## Naming Conventions
- **Components:** PascalCase directories and files: `ComponentName.tsx`
- **Co-located files:** `ComponentName.module.scss`, `ComponentName.models.ts`, `ComponentName.utils.ts`, `ComponentName.reducer.ts`, `ComponentName.lazy.tsx`
- **Barrel exports:** `index.ts` re-exporting from the main file
- **Path aliases:** `@/*` → `src/*`, `@core/*` → `src/core/*`, `@libs/*` → `src/libs/*`, `@widgets/*` → `src/widgets/*`

## Styling Rules
- Use **Tailwind utility classes** for layout/spacing/flex and **SCSS Modules** for complex component styles
- Global design tokens live in `src/app/styles/theme/` as CSS custom properties (`--color-*`, `--font-*`, `--radius-*`, etc.)
- Tailwind v4 tokens defined in `@theme { }` block in `globals.scss`
- Combine classes with `classnames` or `tailwind-merge`
- Prettier sorts Tailwind classes via `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss`

## Data Fetching Patterns
- **Server Components (RSC):** Call API classes directly → `prefetchQuery` → `dehydrate` → pass state to `SSRReactQueryProvider`
- **Client Components:** `useQuery` / `useMutation` hooks from `src/core/api/hooks/`
- **Auth on API calls:** `useAuth().getToken()` → `withAuth(token)` in API calls
- **API classes** are static: `TopicApi.getTopics()`, `ArgumentApi.getArguments()`, etc.
- **QueryClient defaults:** `staleTime: 60s`, `refetchOnMount: false`, `refetchOnReconnect: false`

## Routing
- App Router under `src/app/[locale]/`
- Routes: `/topics/[topicId]`, `/topics/.../versions/[versionId]/...`, `/arguments/[argumentId]`, `/search`, `/new-opinion`, `/sign/[[...rest]]`
- Locale-aware navigation via `useLocaleRouter` hook

## i18n
- Namespaces: `common`, `metadata`, `mainPage`, `topicVersion`, `searchPage`, `consensusPage`, `argumentPage`, `newOpinionPage`
- Server: `initServerI18n` for metadata
- Client: `useTranslation` with namespace

## Formatting & Linting
- **ESLint 9** flat config (`eslint.config.mjs`) with TypeScript, React, Next, import sorting, unused-imports
- **Prettier:** single quotes, JSX single quotes, 120 char width, trailing comma es5, Tailwind plugin
- **No pre-commit hooks** (no husky/lint-staged)
- **No test suite** configured

## CI/CD
- GitHub Actions: self-hosted deploy on `main` push
- Build: `yarn install` → `yarn build` → copy standalone → systemd restart on port 6062

## Key Env Variables
- `NEXT_HTTP_URL` — Backend API base URL (used as Axios baseURL)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` — Clerk public key
- `CLERK_SECRET_KEY` — Clerk secret
- `SERVER_API_BASE_URL` — Dev-only proxy target for `/api/*` rewrites

## Important Patterns to Follow
1. New UI primitives go in `src/libs/ui-components/`
2. New domain widgets go in `src/widgets/` (or `src/widgets/PageWidgets/` if page-specific)
3. New API endpoints: add static method to appropriate class in `src/core/api/apis/`, add React Query hook in `src/core/api/hooks/`
4. New domain types go in `src/core/models/`, API response types in `src/core/api/models/`
5. Always use path aliases (`@/`, `@core/`, `@libs/`, `@widgets/`)
6. Lazy-load heavy widgets with `next/dynamic`
7. Use `FC<Props>` typing pattern for components
8. Keep co-located `.models.ts` files for component-specific types
